            "traditional": "\u5187"
        },
        {
            "text": "\u6709 can be used in at least three ways: <ol>\n  <li>Expressing possession</li>\n  <li>Expressing existence</li>\n  <li>As an auxiliary verb WIP</li>\n  <li>To introduce indefinite noun phrases WIP</li>\n</ol>\n"
        },
        {
            "text": "<h2> Expressing possession </h2>"
        },
        {
            "text": "\u6709 can be used as 'to have' in english. Since its a normal verb the basic structure is:<br> Subject + \u6709 + Object\n"
        },
        {
            "text": "Some examples might be:\n"
        },
        {
            "text": "\u6211\u5187\u9322",
            "jyutping": "ngo5 mou5 cin2",
            "translation": "I don't have money",
            "pinyin": "wo3 you3 qian2",
            "simplified": "\u6211\u5187\u94b1",
            "traditional": "\u6211\u5187\u9322"
        },
        {
            "text": "\u4f60\u6709\u623f\u5b50\u5417",
            "jyutping": "nei5 jau5 fong4 zi2 aa3",
            "translation": "Do you have a house?",
            "pinyin": "ni1 you3 fang2 zi ma",
            "simplified": "\u4f60\u6709\u623f\u5b50\u5417",
            "traditional": "\u4f60\u6709\u623f\u5b50\u5417"
        },
        {
            "text": "<h2> Expressing existence </h2>"
        },
        {
            "text": "\u6709 can also be used to express existence like the Spanish 'hay'. This is similar to the English 'There is' or 'There are'. Similarly \u5187 is used to express 'There is not'.\n"
        },
        {
            "text": "The structure is also similar:<br> Place + \u6709 + Object\n"
        },
        {
            "text": "\u6211\u5bb6\u6709\u597d\u591a\u5c0f\u72d7",
